Delicious and affordable restaurant. The workers are very nice, and the food is made fast.
My Mysore masala dosa had cashews and raisins in it which was a yummy surprise! I ordered this for my dinner, and it was plentiful food for me! I was very full and content after 😊😊😊
This is old small restaurant.we often go there.We love Goan bun bhaji.But this time bhaji was not tasty.vegcutlet is good.Its vegetarian restaurant.parking problem is here.Good for small group s.

Quick, affordable 💵,fast veg🥗 restaurant🍴located beside a very busy road🛣️... So here is the review:

Staff🧒: Prompt and responsive😊 staff as servers and cleaners✨ with table service
Interior💺:  That can accommodate easily 50 people🎎.. Nice marble tables with firm steel seatings that are always clean...With fans for ventilations and has a separate AC room too that can take a out 20people 😅
Parking🚗: Public parking infront of the restaurant🛣️ which is easier for 2 wheelers🏍️ but not for cars🚗...they will need to park across the road somewhere... Depends on rush hour traffic too🚦
Timings⌚: Opens early at 8am and closes by 10pm with no lunchtime break.. timings may vary sometimes 😅
Restaurant🏪: Contains  mostly freshly prepared hot♨️ South🍛 Indian food items like Dosa🥞, Idlis🍙,Vadas🥔, Puri with many Bhaji options🍪😊that are good for taste and very affordable 💵 too... It also has Veg thalis🍛 in the afternoon time between 1pm to 2pm.. Serves a lot of hot beverages too☕ like tea coffee ☕ and other coolers🍹...It also has a juice counter🍇🍉🍋🍊 ... It has Chaat and other items in the evenings🌇 after 4pm...Try their Dahi shev Puri that is available after 4pm😋
Pricing💵: Reasonably priced and affordable 🥞 for its location
Crowd: Local and mostly college students and employees from nearby👨‍🏭👷‍♀️👷‍♂️

Usually it is a busy place any time of the day or night... At the most people halt for 30mins max... People drop by all the time for breakfast, lunch and dinner🙂... The rest can be seen in the photos attached below😅
